###Block: Feral Gargun
Mountain Movement			KEY:Feral Gargun ~ Mountain Movement				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Feral Gargun Race Trait.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Because feral garguns practically live on the ledges and cliffs of the most forbidding mountains, they are particularly adept at negotiating mountain hazards. A feral gargun can make standing long jumps and high jumps as if they were running long jumps and high jumps. He can engage in accelerated climbing (climbing half his speed as a move action) without taking the -5 penalty on the Climb check.
Resistance to Cold 5		KEY:Feral Gargun ~ Resistance to Cold 5				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Feral Gargun Race Trait.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Feral garguns have adapted to the harsh conditions of their homelands, growing a tough hide and thick fur to protect them from low temperatures. They can ignore the fi rst 5 points of cold damage dealt by any attack, whether mundane or magical.
Natural Armor			KEY:Feral Gargun ~ Natural Armor					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Feral Gargun Race Trait.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:A feral gargun's tough hide and thick fur protect him from harm, giving him a +2 natural armor bonus to AC.
Natural Attack			KEY:Feral Gargun ~ Natural Attack					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Feral Gargun Race Trait.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:A feral gargun has two claw attacks, each dealing 1d6 points of damage. A feral gargun armed with a weapon sometimes uses the weapon as its primary attack and a claw as a natural secondary attack (provided it has a claw free to make the secondary attack).
Goliath Blood			KEY:Feral Gargun ~ Goliath Blood					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Feral Gargun Race Trait.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:For all effects related to race, a feral gargun is considered a goliath. Feral garguns, for example, are just as vulnerable to special effects that affect goliaths as their goliath ancestors are, and they can use magic items that are only usable by goliaths.

#
Weapon and Armor Proficiency	KEY:Feral Gargun ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Feral Gargun Race Trait.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.92	DESC:A feral gargun is profi cient with all simple weapons, but has no profi ciency with any armor or shield.
Acclimated				KEY:Feral Gargun ~ Acclimated							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Feral Gargun Race Trait.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.92	DESC:Beginning at 2nd level, feral garguns become acclimated to life at high altitude. They don't take the penalties for altitude described on page 90 of the Dungeon Master's Guide. Unlike other denizens of the mountains, feral garguns don't lose their acclimation to high altitude even if they spend months or years at lower elevations.
Powerful Build			KEY:Feral Gargun ~ Powerful Build						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Feral Gargun Race Trait.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.92	DESC:From 3rd level on, feral garguns grow large enough that, although they are Medium creatures, they are treated as Large for many purposes. See the Powerful Build racial trait described above for details.

