Weapon and Armor Proficiency	KEY:Battlesmith ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Battlesmith Class Feature.SpecialQuality										DESC:Battlesmiths gain no proficiency with any weapon or armor.																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.98
One with the Hammer		KEY:Battlesmith ~ One with the Hammer		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Battlesmith Class Feature.SpecialQuality							DESC:A battlesmith's long hours at the forge grant her a special bond with a hammer. When wielding a warhammer that she has crafted herself, a battlesmith adds her Wisdom bonus as a bonus to the damage dealt by the weapon.																																																																												BONUS:WEAPONPROF=Warhammer|DAMAGE|WIS	SOURCEPAGE:p.98
Secrets of the Forge		KEY:Battlesmith ~ Secrets of the Forge		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Battlesmith Class Feature.SpecialQuality							DESC:A battlesmith learns some of the great dwarven secrets of forging weapons and armor. A battlesmith receives Craft Magic Arms and Armor as a bonus feat, regardless of her caster level. Multiply the battle smith's class level by 3 to determine her effective caster level for the purpose of creating magic arms and armor (this benefit stacks with any other caster levels the battlesmith might have). The battlesmith must still meet any other prerequisites for the item's creation. This stipulation might mean that she needs the assistance of other characters to complete the creation of an item.																					SOURCEPAGE:p.98
Flesh of My Flesh			KEY:Battlesmith ~ Flesh of My Flesh			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Battlesmith Class Feature.SpecialQuality	DEFINE:FleshOfMyFleshACBonus|0	DESC:No armor fits so well as that created by a battlesmith for her own use. When wearing heavy armor that she has crafted herself, a battlesmith of 2nd level or higher gains a +1 sacred bonus to Armor Class. This bonus increases to +2 at 4th level.																																																											BONUS:COMBAT|AC|FleshOfMyFleshACBonus|TYPE=Sacred|PREEQUIP:1,Armor.Heavy								SOURCEPAGE:p.98	ASPECT:NAME|Flesh of My Flesh +%1|FleshOfMyFleshACBonus	BONUS:VAR|FleshOfMyFleshACBonus|1+(BattlesmithLVL>=4)
Forged in Fire			KEY:Battlesmith ~ Forged in Fire			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Battlesmith Class Feature.SpecialQuality							DESC:At 3rd level, a battlesmith becomes inured to the effects of fatigue and exhaustion, and can ignore their effects for a number of hours equal to her class level. At the end of this time, if the condition remains, the battlesmith succumbs to the effects.																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.98
Tempered in Blood			KEY:Battlesmith ~ Tempered in Blood			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Battlesmith Class Feature.SpecialQuality							DESC:Once per day, a 5th-level battlesmith can attempt to resist the damage from a single blow. The battlesmith can attempt a Fortitude save (DC 10 + damage dealt) when struck and damaged by a melee attack with a weapon or natural attack (but not by a spell or other effect). If the save succeeds, the battlesmith takes only half damage from the blow; if it fails, she takes normal damage. The battlesmith must be aware of the attack and able to react to it to use this ability. If she is denied her Dexterity bonus to AC, she can't use this ability.																													SOURCEPAGE:p.98



